				<section id="season2">
					<h2>NEW Season 2 Changes</h2>
					<p>
						Patch 11.1 included changes for Protection Paladin that were targeted at Mythic+.  Strength in Adversity had the amount of parry it grants reduced from 5% to 3%, which reduces how much parry chance Protection can achieve when fighting multiple targets. Parry primarily affects melee swings and becomes significant the more melees you face, making this change less likely to affect raid settings where parry is not as important. As it happens,  Strength in Adversity is not presently included in any raid builds outside of niche situations.

						We also received a damage nerf through  Refining Fire having its power reduced. Once again, this affects Mythic+ more than raids, as the damage of  Refining Fire was a significant part of the damage breakdown in AoE.

						Finally,  Uther's Counsel was nerfed from 30% to 15%, meaning you'll have less cooldown availability.
					</p>
