						<section id="leveling">
							<h2>Leveling</h2>

							<h3>Leveling Tips for Protection Paladin</h3>

							<ul>
								<li>Focus on spamming Consecration to damage large packs of enemies efficiently. Consecration uptime is critical for both survivability and DPS while leveling.</li>
								<li>Use Shield of the Righteous whenever you have Holy Power ready. It boosts your armor massively and prevents a lot of damage, allowing for bigger pulls.</li>
								<li>Judgment should be used on cooldown to generate Holy Power and debuff targets (especially if you have Greater Judgment talented for extra spender damage).</li>
								<li>Use Hammer of the Righteous or Blessed Hammer as your filler ability when waiting for cooldowns.</li>
								<li>Keep Divine Steed handy for fast repositioning, pulling packs faster, and escaping when necessary. Pick up Cavalier talent early for two charges of Divine Steed.</li>
								<li>Dungeon leveling is highly recommended. Protection Paladin can tank multiple enemies very efficiently in dungeons, leading to fast XP and gear upgrades.</li>
								<li>While solo questing, take talents that boost your survivability and Holy Power generation early on rather than focusing only on damage talents.</li>
								<li>Make sure to maintain Consecration uptime especially when you talent into Consecrated Ground — it slows enemies standing inside and helps you kite when needed.</li>
								<li>Save Avenger's Shield and Divine Toll (if talented) for dangerous mobs or multiple targets that can overwhelm you.</li>
								<li>Don't be afraid to use Word of Glory to heal up between pulls, especially when you have free casts from Shining Light procs.</li>
							</ul>

